3479,3,2,1,3479,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{3478}}3478%%:--Israel.','ישראל','yis-raw-ale''','Yisra''el'

3482,3,2,1,3482,'feminine of {{3481}}3481%%; a Jisreelitess or female descendant of Jisrael:--Israelitish.','ישראלית','yis-reh-ay-leeth''','Yisr''eliyth'
3483,3,2,1,3483,'feminine or {{3477}}3477%%; rectitude:--uprightness.','ישרה','yish-raw''','yishrah'
3484,3,2,1,3484,'from {{3474}}3474%%; upright; Jeshurun, a symbol. name for Israel:--Jeshurun.','ישרון','yesh-oo-roon''','Yshuruwn'

3486,3,2,1,3486,'from an unused root meaning to blanch;  gray-haired, i.e. an aged man:--stoop for age.','ישש','yaw-shaysh''','yashesh'

3492,3,2,1,3492,'from {{3498}}3498%%; redundant; Jattir, a place in Palestine:--Jattir.','יתיר','yat-teer''','Yattiyr'

3494,3,2,1,3494,'probably from {{8518}}8518%%; it will hang, i.e. be high; Jithlah, a place in Palestine:--Jethlah.','יתלה','yith-law''','Yithlah'
3495,3,2,1,3495,'from the same as {{3490}}3490%%; orphanage; Jithmah, an Israelite:--Ithmah.','יתמה','yith-maw''','Yithmah'
3496,3,2,1,3496,'from an unused root meaning to endure, and {{410}}410%%; continued of God; Jathniel, an Israelite:--Jathniel.','יתניאל','yath-nee-ale''','Yathniy''el'
3497,3,2,1,3497,'from the same as {{8577}}8577%%; extensive; Jithnan, a place in Palestine:--Ithnan.','יתנן','yith-nawn''','Yithnan'
3498,3,2,1,3498,'a primitive root; to jut over or exceed; by implication, to excel; (intransitively) to remain or be left; causatively, to leave, cause to abound, preserve:--excel, leave (a remnant), left behind, too much, make plenteous, preserve, (be, let) remain(-der, -ing, - nant), reserve, residue, rest.','יתר','yaw-thar''','yathar'
3499,3,2,1,3499,'from {{3498}}3498%%; properly, an overhanging, i.e. (by implication) an excess, superiority, remainder; also a small rope (as hanging free):--+ abundant, cord, exceeding, excellancy(-ent), what they leave, that hath left, plentifully, remnant, residue, rest, string, with.','יתר','yeh''-ther','yether'
3500,3,2,1,3500,'the same as {{3499}}3499%%; Jether, the name of five or six Israelites and of one Midianite:--Jether, Jethro. Compare {{3503}}3503%%.','יתר','yeh''-ther','Yether'

3510,3,2,1,3510,'a primitive root; properly, to feel pain; by implication, to grieve; figuratively, to spoil:--grieving, mar, have pain, make sad (sore), (be) sorrowful.','כאב','kaw-ab''','ka''ab'
3511,3,2,1,3511,'from {{3510}}3510%%; suffering (physical or mental), adversity:--grief, pain, sorrow.','כאב','keh-abe''','k''eb'

3513,3,2,1,3513,'or kabed {kaw-bade''}; a primitive root; to be heavy, i.e. in a bad sense (burdensome, severe, dull) or in a good sense (numerous, rich, honorable; causatively, to make weighty (in the same two senses):--abounding with, more grievously afflict, boast, be chargeable, X be dim, glorify, be (make) glorious (things), glory, (very) great, be grievous, harden, be (make) heavy, be heavier, lay heavily, (bring to, come to, do, get, be had in) honour (self), (be) honourable (man), lade, X more be laid, make self many, nobles, prevail, promote (to honour), be rich, be (go) sore, stop.','כבד','kaw-bad''','kabad'
3514,3,2,1,3514,'from {{3513}}3513%%; weight, multitude, vehemence:  -grievousness, heavy, great number.','כבד','ko''-bed','kobed'
3515,3,2,1,3515,'from {{3513}}3513%%; heavy; figuratively in a good sense (numerous) or in a bad sense (severe, difficult, stupid):--(so) great, grievous, hard(-ened), (too) heavy(-ier), laden, much, slow, sore, thick.','כבד','kaw-bade''','kabed'
3516,3,2,1,3516,'the same as {{3515}}3515%%; the liver (as the heaviest of the viscera):--liver.','כבד','kaw-bade''','kabed'
3517,3,2,1,3517,'feminine of {{3515}}3515%%; difficulty:--X heavily.','כבדת','keb-ay-dooth''','kbeduth'
3518,3,2,1,3518,' a primitive root;  to expire or (causatively) to extinguish (fire, light, anger):--go (put) out, quench.','כבה','kaw-baw''','kabah'

3520,3,2,1,3520,'irreg. feminine passive participle of {{3513}}3513%%; weightiness, i.e. magnificence, wealth:--carriage, all glorious, stately.','כבודה','keb-ood-daw''','kbuwddah'
3521,3,2,1,3521,'from the same as {{3525}}3525%% in the sense of limitation; sterile; Cabul, the name of two places in Palestine:--Cabul.','כבול','kaw-bool''','Kabuwl'
3522,3,2,1,3522,'from an unused root meaning to heap up; hilly; Cabon, a place in Palestine:--Cabbon.','כבון','kab-bone''','Kabbown'
3523,3,2,1,3523,'from {{3527}}3527%% in the original sense of plaiting; a matrass (of intertwined materials):--pillow.','כביר','keb-eer','kbiyr'
3524,3,2,1,3524,'from {{3527}}3527%%; vast, whether in extent (figuratively, of power, mighty; of time, aged), or in number, many:--+ feeble, mighty, most, much, strong, valiant.','כביר','kab-beer''','kabbiyr'
3525,3,2,1,3525,'from an unused root meaning to twine or braid together; a fetter:--fetter.','כבל','keh''-bel','kebel'
3526,3,2,1,3526,'a primitive root; to trample; hence, to wash (properly, by stamping with the feet), whether literal (including the fulling process) or figurative:--fuller, wash(-ing).','כבס','kaw-bas''','kabac'
3527,3,2,1,3527,'a primitive root; properly, to plait together, i.e. (figuratively) to augment (especially in number or quantity, to accumulate):--in abundance, multiply.','כבר','kaw-bar''','kabar'
3528,3,2,1,3528,'from {{3527}}3527%%; properly, extent of time, i.e. a great while; hence, long ago, formerly, hitherto:--already, (seeing that which), now.','כבר','keb-awr''','kbar'
3529,3,2,1,3529,'the same as {{3528}}3528%%; length; Kebar, a river of Mesopotamia:--Chebar. Compare {{2249}}2249%%.','כבר','keb-awr''','Kbar'
3530,3,2,1,3530,'feminine of {{3528}}3528%%; properly, length, i.e. a measure (of uncertain dimension):--X little.','כברה','kib-raw''','kibrah'
3531,3,2,1,3531,'from {{3527}}3527%% in its original sense; a sieve (as netted):--sieve.','כברה','keb-aw-raw''','kbarah'
3532,3,2,1,3532,'from an unused root meaning to dominate; a ram (just old enough to butt):--lamb, sheep.','כבש','keh-bes''','kebes'
3533,3,2,1,3533,'a primitive root; to tread down; hence, negatively, to disregard; positively, to conquer, subjugate, violate:--bring into bondage, force, keep under, subdue, bring into subjection.','כבש','kaw-bash''','kabash'
3534,3,2,1,3534,'from {{3533}}3533%%; a footstool (as trodden upon):  -footstool.','כבש','keh''-besh','kebesh'
3535,3,2,1,3535,'or kabsah {kab-saw''}; feminine of {{3532}}3532%%; a ewe:--(ewe) lamb.','כבשה','kib-saw''','kibsah'
3536,3,2,1,3536,'from {{3533}}3533%%; a smelting furnace (as reducing metals):--furnace.','כבשן','kib-shawn''','kibshan'
3537,3,2,1,3537,'from an unused root meaning to deepen; properly, a pail; but generally of earthenware; a jar for domestic purposes:--barrel, pitcher.','כד','kad','kad'
3538,3,2,1,3538,'(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{3576}}3576%%; false:  -lying.','כדב','ked-ab''','kdab'
3539,3,2,1,3539,'from the same as {{3537}}3537%% in the sense of striking fire from a metal forged; a sparkling gem, probably the ruby:--agate.','כדכד','kad-kobe''','kadkod'
3540,3,2,1,3540,'of foreign origin; Kedorlaomer, an early Persian king:--Chedorlaomer.','כדרלעמר','ked-or-law-o''-mer','Kdorla`omer'
3541,3,2,1,3541,'from the prefix k and {{1931}}1931%%; properly, like this, i.e. by implication, (of manner) thus (or so also (of place) here (or hither or (of time) now:--also, here, + hitherto, like, on the other side, so (and much), such, on that manner, (on) this (manner, side, way, way and that way), + mean while, yonder.','כה','ko','koh'
3542,3,2,1,3542,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{3541}}3541%%:--hitherto.','כה','kaw','kah'
3543,3,2,1,3543,' a primitive root; to be weak, i.e. (figuratively) to despond (causatively, rebuke), or (of light, the eye) to grow dull:-- darken, be dim, fail, faint, restrain, X utterly.','כהה','kaw-haw''','kahah'
3544,3,2,1,3544,'from {{3543}}3543%%; feeble, obscure:--somewhat dark, darkish, wax dim, heaviness, smoking.','כהה','kay-heh''','keheh'
3545,3,2,1,3545,'feminine of {{3544}}3544%%; properly, a weakening; figuratively, alleviation, i.e. cure:--healing.','כהה','kay-haw''','kehah'
3546,3,2,1,3546,'(Aramaic) a root corresponding to {{3201}}3201%% and {{3557}}3557%%; to be able:--be able, could.','כהל','keh-hal''','khal'
3547,3,2,1,3547,'a primitive root, apparently meaning to mediate in religious services; but used only as denominative from {{3548}}3548%%; to officiate as a priest; figuratively, to put on regalia:--deck, be (do the office of a, execute the, minister in the) priest(''s office).','כהן','kaw-han''','kahan'

3549,3,2,1,3549,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{3548}}3548%%:--priest.','כהן','kaw-hane''','kahen'
3550,3,2,1,3550,'from {{3547}}3547%%; priesthood:--priesthood, priest''s office.','כהנה','keh-hoon-naw''','khunnah'
3551,3,2,1,3551,'(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{3854}}3854%% in the sense of piercing; a window (as a perforation):--window.','כו','kav','kav'
3552,3,2,1,3552,'of foreign derivation; Kub, a country near Egypt:--Chub.','כוב','koob','Kuwb'
3553,3,2,1,3553,'from an unused root meaning to be high or rounded; a helmet (as arched):--helmet. Compare {{6959}}6959%%.','כובע','ko''-bah','kowba`'

3555,3,2,1,3555,'from {{3554}}3554%%; a branding:--burning.','כויה','kev-ee-yaw''','kviyah'
3556,3,2,1,3556,'probably from the same as {{3522}}3522%% (in the sense of rolling) or {{3554}}3554%% (in the sense of blazing a star (as round or as shining figuratively, a prince:--star((-gazer)).','כוכב','ko-kawb''','kowkab'
3557,3,2,1,3557,'a primitive root; properly, to keep in; hence, to measure; figuratively, to maintain (in various senses):--(be able to, can) abide, bear, comprehend, contain, feed, forbearing, guide, hold(-ing in), nourish(-er), be present, make provision, receive, sustain, provide sustenance (victuals).','כול','kool','kuwl'
3558,3,2,1,3558,'from an unused root meaning to store away; a jewel (probably gold beads):--tablet.','כומז','koo-mawz''','kuwmaz'
3559,3,2,1,3559,'a primitive root; properly, to be erect (i.e. stand perpendicular hence (causatively) to set up, in a great variety of applications, whether literal (establish, fix, prepare, apply), or figurative (appoint, render sure, proper or prosperous):--certain(-ty), confirm, direct, faithfulness, fashion, fasten, firm, be fitted, be fixed, frame, be meet, ordain, order, perfect, (make) preparation, prepare (self), provide, make provision, (be, make) ready, right, set (aright, fast, forth), be stable, (e-)stablish, stand, tarry, X very deed.','כון','koon','kuwn'
3560,3,2,1,3560,'probably from {{3559}}3559%%; established; Kun, a place in Syria:--Chun.','כון','koon','Kuwn'
3561,3,2,1,3561,'from {{3559}}3559%%; something prepared, i.e. a sacrificial wafer:--cake.','כון','kav-vawn''','kavvan'
3562,3,2,1,3562,'from {{3559}}3559%% and {{3050}}3050%%; Jah has sustained; Conanjah, the name of two Israelites:--Conaniah, Cononiah. Compare {{3663}}3663%%.','כונניהו','ko-nan-yaw''-hoo','Kownanyahuw'
3563,3,2,1,3563,'from an unused root meaning to hold together; a cup (as a container), often figuratively, a lot (as if a potion also some unclean bird, probably an owl (perhaps from the cup-like cavity of its eye):--cup, (small) owl. Compare {{3599}}3599%%.','כוס','koce','kowc'
3564,3,2,1,3564,'from an unused root meaning properly, to dig through; a pot or furnace (as if excavated):--furnace. Compare {{3600}}3600%%.','כור','koor','kuwr'
3565,3,2,1,3565,'from {{3564}}3564%% and {{6227}}6227%%; furnace of smoke; Cor-Ashan, a place in Palestine:--Chor-ashan.','כור  עשן','kore aw-shawn''','Kowr`Ashan'
3566,3,2,1,3566,'or (Ezra {{1}}1%%:{{1}}1%% (last time),{{2}}2%%) Koresh {ko''-resh}; from the Persians; Koresh (or Cyrus), the Persian king:--Cyrus.','כורש','ko''-resh','Kowresh'
3567,3,2,1,3567,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{3566}}3566%%:--Cyrus.','כורש','ko''-resh','Kowresh'
3568,3,2,1,3568,'probably of foreign origin; Cush (or Ethiopia), the name of a son of Ham, and of his territory; also of an Israelite:--Chush, Cush, Ethiopia.','כוש','koosh','Kuwsh'
3569,3,2,1,3569,'patronymically from {{3568}}3568%%; a Cushite, or descendant of Cush:--Cushi, Cushite, Ethiopian(-s).','כושי','koo-shee''','Kuwshiy'
3570,3,2,1,3570,'the same as {{3569}}3569%%; Cushi, the name of two Israelites:--Cushi.','כושי','koo-shee''','Kuwshiy'
3571,3,2,1,3571,'feminine of {{3569}}3569%%; a Cushite woman:  -Ethiopian.','כושית','koo-sheeth''','Kuwshiyth'
3572,3,2,1,3572,'perhaps from {{3568}}3568%%; Cushan, a region of Arabia:  -Cushan.','כושן','koo-shawn''','Kuwshan'
3573,3,2,1,3573,'apparently from {{3572}}3572%% and the dual of {{7564}}7564%%; Cushan of double wickedness; Cushan-Rishathajim, a Mesopotamian king:--Chushan-rishathayim.','כושן  רשעתים','koo-shan'' rish-aw-thah''-yim','Kuwshan Rish`athayim'
3574,3,2,1,3574,'from {{3787}}3787%%; prosperity; in plural freedom:  -X chain.','כושרה','ko-shaw-raw''','kowsharah'
3575,3,2,1,3575,'or (feminine) Kuwthah {koo-thaw''}; of foreign origin; Cuth or Cuthah, a province of Assyria:--Cuth.','כות','kooth','Kuwth'
3576,3,2,1,3576,'a primitive root; to lie (i.e. deceive), literally or figuratively:--fail, (be found a, make a) liar, lie, lying, be in vain.','כזב','kaw-zab''','kazab'
3577,3,2,1,3577,' from {{3576}}3576%%;  falsehood; literally (untruth) or figuratively (idol):--deceitful, false, leasing, + liar, lie, lying.','כזב','kaw-zawb''','kazab'
3578,3,2,1,3578,'from {{3576}}3576%%; fallacious; Cozeba, a place in Palestine:--Choseba.','כזבא','ko-zeb-aw''','Kozba'''
3579,3,2,1,3579,'from {{3576}}3576%%; false; Cozbi, a Midianitess:--Cozbi.','כזבי','koz-bee''','Kozbiy'
3580,3,2,1,3580,'from {{3576}}3576%%; falsified; Kezib, a place in Palestine:--Chezib.','כזיב','kez-eeb''','Kziyb'
3581,3,2,1,3581,'or (Dan. {{11}}11%%:{{6}}6%%) kowach {ko''-akh}; from an unused root meaning to be firm; vigor, literally (force, in a good or a bad sense) or figuratively (capacity, means, produce also (from its hardiness) a large lizard:  -ability, able, chameleon, force, fruits, might, power(-ful), strength, substance, wealth.','כח','ko''-akh','koach'
3582,3,2,1,3582,'a primitive root; to secrete, by act or word; hence (intensively) to destroy:--conceal, cut down (off), desolate, hide.','כחד','kaw-khad''','kachad'
3583,3,2,1,3583,'a primitive root; to paint (with stibium):  -paint.','כחל','kaw-khal''','kachal'
3584,3,2,1,3584,'a primitive root; to be untrue, in word (to lie, feign, disown) or deed (to disappoint, fail, cringe):--deceive, deny, dissemble, fail, deal falsely, be found liars, (be-)lie, lying, submit selves.','כחש','kaw-khash''','kachash'

3586,3,2,1,3586,'from {{3584}}3584%%; faithless:--lying.','כחש','kekh-awsh''','kechash'
3587,3,2,1,3587,'from {{3554}}3554%%; a brand or scar:--burning.','כי','kee','kiy'
3588,3,2,1,3588,'a primitive particle (the full form of the prepositional prefix) indicating causal relations of all kinds, antecedent or consequent; (by implication) very widely used as a relative conjunction or adverb (as below often largely modified by other particles annexed:--and, + (forasmuch, inasmuch, where-)as, assured(-ly), + but, certainly, doubtless, + else, even, + except, for, how, (because, in, so, than) that, + nevertheless, now, rightly, seeing, since, surely, then, therefore, + (al- )though, + till, truly, + until, when, whether, while, whom, yea, yet.','כי','kee','kiy'
3589,3,2,1,3589,'from a primitive root meaning to strike: a crushing; figuratively, calamity:--destruction.','כיד','keed','kiyd'
3590,3,2,1,3590,'from the same as {{3589}}3589%% (compare {{3539}}3539%% properly, something struck off, i.e. a spark (as struck):--spark.','כידוד','kee-dode''','kiydowd'
3591,3,2,1,3591,'from the same as {{3589}}3589%%; properly, something to strike with, i.e. a dart (perhaps smaller that {{2595}}2595%%):--lance, shield, spear, target.','כידון','kee-dohn''','kiydown'
3592,3,2,1,3592,'the same as {{3591}}3591%%; Kidon, a place in Palestine:  -Chidon.','כידון','kee-dohn''','Kiydown'

7965,3,2,1,7965,'or shalom {shaw-lome''}; from {{7999}}7999%%; safe, i.e. (figuratively) well, happy, friendly; also (abstractly) welfare, i.e. health, prosperity, peace:--X do, familiar, X fare, favour, + friend, X great, (good) health, (X perfect, such as be at) peace(-able, -ably), prosper(-ity, -ous), rest, safe(-ty), salute, welfare, (X all is, be) well, X wholly.','שלום','shaw-lome''','shalowm'
7966,3,2,1,7966,'or shillum {shil-loom''}; from {{7999}}7999%%; a requital, i.e. (secure) retribution, (venal) a fee:--recompense, reward.','שלום','shil-loom''','shilluwm'
7967,3,2,1,7967,'or (shorter) Shallum {shal-loom''}; the same as {{7966}}7966%%; Shallum, the name of fourteen Israelites:--Shallum.','שלום','shal-loom''','Shalluwm'
7968,3,2,1,7968,'probably for {{7967}}7967%%; Shallun, an Israelite:--Shallum.','שלון','shal-loon''','Shalluwn'
7969,3,2,1,7969,'or shalosh {shaw-loshe''}; masculine shlowshah {shel-o-shaw''}; or shloshah {shel-o-shaw''}; a primitive number; three; occasionally (ordinal) third, or (multipl.) thrice:--+ fork, + often(-times), third, thir(-teen, -teenth), three, + thrice. Compare {{7991}}7991%%.','שלוש','shaw-loshe''','shalowsh'
7970,3,2,1,7970,'or shloshiym {shel-o-sheem''}; multiple of {{7969}}7969%%; thirty; or (ordinal) thirtieth:--thirty, thirtieth. Compare {{7991}}7991%%.','שלשים','shel-o-sheem''','shlowshiym'
7971,3,2,1,7971,'a primitive root; to send away, for, or out (in a great variety of applications):--X any wise, appoint, bring (on the way), cast (away, out), conduct, X earnestly, forsake, give (up), grow long, lay, leave, let depart (down, go, loose), push away, put (away, forth, in, out), reach forth, send (away, forth, out), set, shoot (forth, out), sow, spread, stretch forth (out).','שלח','shaw-lakh''','shalach'
7972,3,2,1,7972,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{7971}}7971%%:--put, send.','שלח','shel-akh''','shlach'
7973,3,2,1,7973,'from {{7971}}7971%%; a missile of attack, i.e. spear; also (figuratively) a shoot of growth; i.e. branch:--dart, plant, X put off, sword, weapon.','שלח','sheh''-lakh','shelach'
7974,3,2,1,7974,'the same as {{7973}}7973%%; Shelach, a postdiluvian patriarch:--Salah, Shelah. Compare {{7975}}7975%%.','שלח','sheh''-lakh','Shelach'
7975,3,2,1,7975,'or (in imitation of {{7974}}7974%%) Shelach (Neh. {{3}}3%%:{{15}}15%%) {sheh''-lakh}; from {{7971}}7971%%; rill; Shiloach, a fountain of Jerusalem:-- Shiloah, Siloah.','שלח','shee-lo''-akh','Shiloach'
7976,3,2,1,7976,'feminine of {{7964}}7964%%; a shoot:--branch.','שלחות','shil-loo-khaw''','shilluchah'
7977,3,2,1,7977,'from {{7973}}7973%%; missive, i.e. armed; Shilchi, an Israelite:--Shilhi.','שלחי','shil-khee''','Shilchiy'
7978,3,2,1,7978,'plural of {{7973}}7973%%; javelins or sprouts; Shilchim, a place in Palestine:--Shilhim.','שלחים','shil-kheem''','Shilchiym'
7979,3,2,1,7979,'from {{7971}}7971%%; a table (as spread out by implication, a meal:--table.','שלחן','shool-khawn''','shulchan'
7980,3,2,1,7980,'a primitive root; to dominate, i.e. govern; by implication, to permit:--(bear, have) rule, have dominion, give (have) power.','שלט','shaw-lat''','shalat'
7981,3,2,1,7981,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{7980}}7980%%:--have the mastery, have power, bear rule, be (make) ruler.','שלט','shel-ate''','shlet'
7982,3,2,1,7982,'from {{7980}}7980%%; probably a shield (as controlling, i.e. protecting the person):--shield.','שלט','sheh''-let','shelet'
7983,3,2,1,7983,'(Aramaic) from {{7980}}7980%%; a potentate; --power.','שלטון','shil-tone''','shiltown'
7984,3,2,1,7984,'(Aramaic) or shilton {shil-tone''}; corresponding to {{7983}}7983%%:--ruler.','שלטן','shil-tone''','shiltown'
7985,3,2,1,7985,'(Aramaic) from {{7981}}7981%%; empire (abstractly or concretely):--dominion.','שלטן','shol-tawn''','sholtan'
7986,3,2,1,7986,'feminine from {{7980}}7980%%; a vixen:--imperious.','שלטת','shal-leh''-teth','shalleteth'
7987,3,2,1,7987,'from {{7951}}7951%%; privacy:--+ quietly.','שלי','shel-ee''','shliy'
7988,3,2,1,7988,'feminine from {{7953}}7953%%; a fetus or babe (as extruded in birth):--young one.','שליה','shil-yaw''','shilyah'
7989,3,2,1,7989,'from {{7980}}7980%%; potent; concretely, a prince or warrior:--governor, mighty, that hath power, ruler.','שליט','shal-leet''','shalliyt'
7990,3,2,1,7990,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{7989}}7989%%; mighty; abstractly, permission; concretely, a premier:--captain, be lawful, rule(- r).','שליט','shal-leet''','shalliyt'
7991,3,2,1,7991,'or shalowsh ( {{1}}1%% Chron. {{11}}11%%:{{11}}11%%; {{12}}12%%:{{18}}18%%) {shaw- loshe''}; or shalosh ({{2}}2%% Sam. {{23}}23%%:{{13}}13%%) {shaw-loshe''}; from {{7969}}7969%%; a triple, i.e. (as a musical instrument) a triangle (or perhaps rather three-stringed lute also (as an indefinite, great quantity) a three-fold measure (perhaps a treble ephah also (as an officer) a general of the third rank (upward, i.e. the highest):--captain, instrument of musick, (great) lord, (great) measure, prince, three (from the margin).','שליש','shaw-leesh''','shaliysh'
7992,3,2,1,7992,'ordinal from {{7969}}7969%%; third; feminine a third (part by extension, a third (day, year or time specifically, a third-story cell):--third (part, rank, time), three (years old).','שלישי','shel-ee-shee''','shliyshiy'
7993,3,2,1,7993,'a primitive root; to throw out, down or away (literally or figuratively):--adventure, cast (away, down, forth, off, out), hurl, pluck, throw.','שלך','shaw-lak','shalak'
7994,3,2,1,7994,'from {{7993}}7993%%; bird of prey, usually thought to be the pelican (from casting itself into the sea):--cormorant.','שלך','shaw-lawk''','shalak'
7995,3,2,1,7995,'from {{7993}}7993%%; a felling (of trees):--when cast.','שלכת','shal-leh''-keth','shalleketh'
7996,3,2,1,7996,'the same as {{7995}}7995%%; Shalleketh, a gate in Jerusalem:--Shalleketh.','שלכת','shal-leh''-keth','Shalleketh'
7997,3,2,1,7997,'a primitive root; to drop or strip; by implication, to plunder:--let fall, make self a prey, X of purpose, (make a, (take)) spoil.','שלל','shaw-lal''','shalal'
7998,3,2,1,7998,'from {{7997}}7997%%; booty:--prey, spoil.','שלל','shaw-lawl''','shalal'
7999,3,2,1,7999,'a primitive root; to be safe (in mind, body or estate figuratively, to be (causatively, make) completed; by implication, to be friendly; by extension, to reciprocate (in various applications):--make amends, (make an) end, finish, full, give again, make good, (re-)pay (again), (make) (to) (be at) peace(-able), that is perfect, perform, (make) prosper(-ous), recompense, render, requite, make restitution, restore, reward, X surely.','שלם','shaw-lam''','shalam'
8000,3,2,1,8000,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{7999}}7999%%; to complete, to restore:--deliver, finish.','שלם','shel-am''','shlam'
8001,3,2,1,8001,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{7965}}7965%%; prosperity:--peace.','שלם','shel-awm''','shlam'
8002,3,2,1,8002,'from {{7999}}7999%%; properly, requital, i.e. a (voluntary) sacrifice in thanks:--peace offering.','שלם','sheh''-lem','shelem'
8003,3,2,1,8003,'from {{7999}}7999%%; complete (literally or figuratively especially friendly:--full, just, made ready, peaceable, perfect(-ed), quiet, Shalem (by mistake for a name), whole.','שלם','shaw-lame''','shalem'
8004,3,2,1,8004,'the same as {{8003}}8003%%; peaceful; Shalem, an early name of Jerusalem:--Salem.','שלם','shaw-lame''','Shalem'
8005,3,2,1,8005,'from {{7999}}7999%%; requital:--recompense.','שלם','shil-lame''','shillem'
8006,3,2,1,8006,'the same as {{8005}}8005%%; Shillem, an Israelite:--Shillem.','שלם','shil-lame''','Shillem'
8007,3,2,1,8007,'probably for {{8008}}8008%%; clothing; Salma, the name of two Israelites:--Salma.','שלמא','sal-maw''','Salma'''
8008,3,2,1,8008,'transp. for {{8071}}8071%%; a dress:--clothes, garment, raiment.','שלמה','sal-maw''','salmah'
8009,3,2,1,8009,'the same as {{8008}}8008%%; clothing; Salmah, an Israelite:--Salmon. Compare {{8012}}8012%%.','שלמה','sal-maw''','Salmah'
8010,3,2,1,8010,'from {{7965}}7965%%; peaceful; Shelomah, David''s successor:--Solomon.','שלמה','shel-o-mo''','Shlomoh'
8011,3,2,1,8011,'feminine of {{7966}}7966%%; retribution:--recompense.','שלמה','shil-loo-maw''','shillumah'
8012,3,2,1,8012,'from {{8008}}8008%%; investiture; Salmon, an Israelite:--Salmon. Compare {{8009}}8009%%.','שלמון','sal-mone''','Salmown'
8013,3,2,1,8013,'feminine plural of {{7965}}7965%%; pacifications; Shelomoth, the name of two Israelites:--Shelomith (from the margin), Shelomoth. Compare {{8019}}8019%%.','שלמות','shel-o-moth''','Shlomowth'
8014,3,2,1,8014,'from {{8008}}8008%%; clothed; Salmai, an Israelite:--Shalmai.','שלמי','sal-mah''-ee','Salmay'
8015,3,2,1,8015,'from {{7965}}7965%%; peaceable; Shelomi, an Israelite:--Shelomi.','שלמי','shel-o-mee''','Shlomiy'
8016,3,2,1,8016,'patronymically from {{8006}}8006%%; a Shilemite (collectively) or descendants of Shillem:--Shillemites.','שלמי','shil-lay-mee''','Shillemiy'
8017,3,2,1,8017,'from {{7965}}7965%% and {{410}}410%%; peace of God; Shelumiel, an Israelite:--Shelumiel.','שלמיאל','shel-oo-mee-ale''','Shlumiy''el'
8018,3,2,1,8018,'or Shelemyahuw {shel-em-yaw''-hoo}; from {{8002}}8002%% and {{3050}}3050%%; thank-offering of Jah; Shelemjah, the name of nine Israelites:--Shelemiah.','שלמיה','shel-em-yaw''','Shelemyah'
8019,3,2,1,8019,'or Shlowmiyth (Ezra {{8}}8%%:{{10}}10%%) {shel-o- meeth''}; from {{7965}}7965%%; peaceableness; Shelomith, the name of five Israelites and three Israelitesses:--Shelomith.','שלמית','shel-o-meeth''','Shlomiyth'
8020,3,2,1,8020,'of foreign derivation; Shalman, a king apparently of Assyria:--Shalman. Compare {{8022}}8022%%.','שלמן','shal-man''','Shalman'
8021,3,2,1,8021,'from {{7999}}7999%%; a bribe:--reward.','שלמנים','shal-mone''','shalmon'
8022,3,2,1,8022,'of foreign derivation; Shalmaneser, an Assyrian king:--Shalmaneser. Comp {{8020}}8020%%.','שלמנאסר','shal-man-eh''-ser','Shalman''ecer'
8023,3,2,1,8023,'the same as {{7888}}7888%%; Shiloni, an Israelite:--Shiloni.','שלני','shee-lo-nee''','Shiloniy'
8024,3,2,1,8024,'from {{7956}}7956%%; a Shelanite (collectively), or descendants of Shelah:--Shelanites.','שלני','shay-law-nee''','Shelaniy'
8025,3,2,1,8025,'a primitive root; to pull out, up or off:--draw (off), grow up, pluck off.','שלף','saw-laf''','shalaph'
8026,3,2,1,8026,'from {{8025}}8025%%; extract; Sheleph, a son of Jokthan:--Sheleph.','שלף','sheh''-lef','shelaph'
8027,3,2,1,8027,'a primitive root perhaps originally to intensify, i.e. treble; but apparently used only as denominative from {{7969}}7969%%, to be (causatively, make) triplicate (by restoration, in portions, strands, days or years):--do the third time, (divide into, stay) three (days, - fold, parts, years old).','שלש','shaw-lash''','shalash'
8028,3,2,1,8028,'from {{8027}}8027%%; triplet; Shelesh, an Israelite:--Shelesh.','שלש','sheh''-lesh','Shelesh'
8029,3,2,1,8029,'from {{8027}}8027%%; a descendant of the third degree, i.e. great grandchild:--third (generation).','שלשים','shil-laysh''','shillesh'
8030,3,2,1,8030,'feminine from the same as {{8028}}8028%%; triplication; Shilshah, an Israelite:--Shilshah.','שלשה','shil-shaw''','Shilshah'
8031,3,2,1,8031,'feminine from {{8027}}8027%%; trebled land; Shalishah, a place in Palestine:--Shalisha.','שלשה','shaw-lee-shaw''','Shalishah'
8032,3,2,1,8032,'or shilshom {shil-shome''}; from the same as {{8028}}8028%%; trebly, i.e. (in time) day before yesterday:--+ before (that time, - time), excellent things (from the margin), + heretofore, three days, + time past.','שלשום','shil-shome''','shilshowm'
8033,3,2,1,8033,'a primitive particle (rather from the relative pronoun, {{834}}834%% there (transferring to time) then; often thither, or thence:--in it, + thence, there (-in, + of, + out), + thither, + whither.','שם','shawm','sham'
8034,3,2,1,8034,'a primitive word (perhaps rather from {{7760}}7760%% through the idea of definite and conspicuous position; compare {{8064}}8064%% an appellation, as a mark or memorial of individuality; by implication honor, authority, character:--+ base, (in-)fame(-ous), named(-d), renown, report.','שם','shame','shem'
8035,3,2,1,8035,'the same as {{8034}}8034%%; name; Shem, a son of Noah (often includ. his posterity):--Sem, Shem.','שם','shame','Shem'
8036,3,2,1,8036,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{8034}}8034%%:--name.','שם','shoom','shum'
8037,3,2,1,8037,'from {{8074}}8074%%; desolation; Shamma, an Israelite:--Shamma.','שמא','sham-maw''','Shamma'''
8038,3,2,1,8038,'apparently from {{8034}}8034%% and {{83}}83%%; name of pinion, i.e. illustrious; Shemeber, a king of Zeboim:--Shemeber.','שמאבר','shem-ay''-ber','Shem''eber'
8039,3,2,1,8039,'perhaps for {{8093}}8093%%; Shimah, an Israelite:--Shimah. Compare {{8043}}8043%%.','שמאה','shim-aw''','Shim''ah'
8040,3,2,1,8040,'or smosl {sem-ole''}; a primitive word (rather perhaps from the same as {{8071}}8071%% (by insertion of the aleph) through the idea of wrapping up properly, dark (as enveloped), i.e. the north; hence (by orientation), the left hand:--left (hand, side).','שמאל','sem-ole''','smo''wl'
8041,3,2,1,8041,'a primitive root (denominative from {{8040}}8040%% to use the left hand or pass in that direction):--(go, turn) (on the, to the) left.','שמאל','saw-mal''','sama''l'
8042,3,2,1,8042,'from {{8040}}8040%%; situated on the left side:--left.','שמאלי','sem-aw-lee''','sma''liy'
8043,3,2,1,8043,'for {{8039}}8039%% (compare {{38}}38%% Shimam, an Israelite:--Shimeam.','שמאם','shim-awm''','Shim''am'
8044,3,2,1,8044,'of uncertain derivation; Shamgar, an Israelite judge:--Shamgar.','שמגר','sham-gar''','Shamgar'
8045,3,2,1,8045,'a primitive root; to desolate:--destory(- uction), bring to nought, overthrow, perish, pluck down, X utterly.','שמד','shaw-mad''','shamad'
8046,3,2,1,8046,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{8045}}8045%%:--consume.','שמד','shem-ad''','shmad'
8047,3,2,1,8047,'from {{8074}}8074%%; ruin; by implication, consternation:--astonishment, desolate(-ion), waste, wonderful thing.','שמה','sham-maw''','shammah'
8048,3,2,1,8048,'the same as {{8047}}8047%%; Shammah, the name of an Edomite and four Israelites:--Shammah.','שמה','sham-maw''','Shammah'
8049,3,2,1,8049,'for {{8048}}8048%%; desolation; Shamhuth, an Israelite:--Shamhuth.','שמהות','sham-hooth''','Shamhuwth'
8050,3,2,1,8050,'from the passive participle of {{8085}}8085%% and {{410}}410%%; heard of God; Shemuel, the name of three Israelites:--Samuel, Shemuel.','שמואל','sehm-oo-ale''','Shmuw''el'
8051,3,2,1,8051,'from {{8074}}8074%%; renowned; Shammua, the name of four Israelites:--Shammua, Shammuah.','שמוע','sham-moo''-ah','Shammuwa`'

8053,3,2,1,8053,'passive participle of {{8103}}8103%%; observed; Shamur, an Israelite:--Shamir (from the margin).','שמור','shaw-moor''','Shamuwr'
8054,3,2,1,8054,'plural of {{8047}}8047%%; ruins; Shammoth, an Israelite:--Shamoth.','שמות','sham-moth''','Shammowth'
8055,3,2,1,8055,'a primitive root; probably to brighten up, i.e. (figuratively) be (causatively, make) blithe or gleesome:--cheer up, be (make) glad, (have, make) joy(-ful), be (make) merry, (cause to, make to) rejoice, X very.','שמח','saw-makh''','samach'
8056,3,2,1,8056,'from {{8055}}8055%%; blithe or gleeful:--(be) glad, joyful, (making) merry((-hearted), -ily), rejoice(-ing).','שמח','saw-may''-akh','sameach'
8057,3,2,1,8057,'from {{8056}}8056%%; blithesomeness or glee, (religious or festival):--X exceeding(-ly), gladness, joy(-fulness), mirth, pleasure, rejoice(-ing).','שמחה','sim-khaw''','simchah'
8058,3,2,1,8058,'a primitive root; to fling down; incipiently to jostle; figuratively, to let alone, desist, remit:--discontinue, overthrow, release, let rest, shake, stumble, throw down.','שמט','shaw-mat''','shamat'
8059,3,2,1,8059,'from {{8058}}8058%%; remission (of debt) or suspension of labor):--release.','שמטה','shem-it-taw''','shmittah'
8060,3,2,1,8060,'from {{8073}}8073%%; destructive; Shammai, the name of three Israelites:--Shammai.','שמי','sham-mah''-ee','Shammay'
8061,3,2,1,8061,'apparently from {{8034}}8034%% and {{3045}}3045%%; name of knowing; Shemida, an Israelite:--Shemida, Shemidah.','שמידע','shem-ee-daw''','Shmiyda`'
8062,3,2,1,8062,'patronymically from {{8061}}8061%%; a Shemidaite (collectively) or descendants of Shemida:--Shemidaites.','שמידעי','shem-ee-daw-ee''','Shmiyda`iy'
8063,3,2,1,8063,'from {{5564}}5564%%; a run (as sustaining the Oriental sitter):--mantle.','שמיכה','sem-ee-kaw''','smiykah'
8064,3,2,1,8064,'dual of an unused singular shameh {shaw-meh''}; from an unused root meaning to be lofty; the sky (as aloft; the dual perhaps alluding to the visible arch in which the clouds move, as well as to the higher ether where the celestial bodies revolve):--air, X astrologer, heaven(-s).','שמים','shaw-mah''-yim','shamayim'
8065,3,2,1,8065,'(Aramaic) corresponding to {{8064}}8064%%:--heaven.','שמין','shaw-mah''-yin','shamayin'
8066,3,2,1,8066,'from {{8083}}8083%%; eight:--eight.','שמיני','shem-ee-nee''','shmiyniy'
8067,3,2,1,8067,'feminine of {{8066}}8066%%; probably an eight-stringed lyre:--Sheminith.','שמינית','shem-ee-neeth''','shmiyniyth'

8070,3,2,1,8070,'or Shmariymowth {shem-aw-ree- moth''}; probably from {{8034}}8034%% and plural of {{7413}}7413%%; name of heights; Shemiramoth, the name of two Israelites:--Shemiramoth.','שמירמות','shem-ee-raw-moth''','Shmiyramowth'
8071,3,2,1,8071,'perhaps by permutation for the feminine of {{5566}}5566%% (through the idea of a cover assuming the shape of the object beneath a dress, especially a mantle:--apparel, cloth(-es, -ing), garment, raiment. Compare {{8008}}8008%%.','שמלה','sim-law''','simlah'

8073,3,2,1,8073,'for {{8014}}8014%%; Shamlai, one of the Nethinim:--Shalmai (from the margin).','שמלי','sham-lah''-ee','Shamlay'
8074,3,2,1,8074,'a primitive root; to stun (or intransitively, grow numb), i.e. devastate or (figuratively) stupefy (both usually in a passive sense):--make amazed, be astonied, (be an) astonish(-ment), (be, bring into, unto, lay, lie, make) desolate(-ion, places), be destitute, destroy (self), (lay, lie, make) waste, wonder.','שמם','shaw-mame''','shamem'

8076,3,2,1,8076,'from {{8074}}8074%%; ruined:--desolate.','שמם','shaw-mame''','shamem'
8077,3,2,1,8077,'or shimamah {shee-mam-aw''}; feminine of {{8076}}8076%%; devastation; figuratively, astonishment:--(laid, X most) desolate(- ion), waste.','שממה','shem-aw-maw''','shmamah'
